
Usage: ./pmdasimplecpu [options]

Libpcp-pmda options:
  -D [ --debug ] [=spec(=-1)]           set debug specification
  -d [ --domain ] n (=129)              domain number to use
  -h [ --help-file ] file (=/var/lib/pcp/pmdas/simplecpu/help)
                                        file containing help text
  -i [ --inet ] port                    use inet port for pmcd comms; conflicts
                                        with -p, -u and -6
  -l [ --log-file ] file (=simplecpu.log)
                                        file to use for logging
  -p [ --pipe ]                         use stdin/stdout for pmcd comms; 
                                        conflicts with -i, -u and -6
  -u [ --unix ] socket                  use named socket for pmcd comms; 
                                        conflicts with -i, -p and -6

Extra options:
  --config file (=/var/lib/pcp/pmdas/simplecpu/config)
                                        load options from config file
  --export-all [=dir(=.)]               export domain, help, pmns and root then
                                        exit
  --export-domain [=file(=-)]           export domain header then exit
  --export-help [=file(=-)]             export help text then exit
  --export-pmns [=file(=-)]             export pmns text then exit
  --export-root [=file(=-)]             export pmns root then exit
  --help                                display this message then exit
  --version                             display version info then exit

